\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 Yes, its definately possible to make those changes...}{
\par \~
\par }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\ul\cf11 1. The mailto}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 you'd simply need to change the form field in }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\cf9 send.htm}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 <FORM name="form1" onsubmit="return validateForm(this)">}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 will change to:}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 <FORM name="form1" }{\cs16\b\i\f1\fs20\cf6 METHOD="POST" ACTION="/cgi-sys/formmail.pl"}{\f1\fs20\cf11  onsubmit="return validateForm(this)">}{
\par \~
\par \~
\par }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\ul\cf11 Note:}{
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 in }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\cf9 js/validate.js}{\f1\fs20\cf11  
\par \~
