\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 post using perl or any other server side language, else the client's mail program will be opened on their side.}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 You can redirect users to the sent.htm file which I included in the Zip file, the variable is already set for that.}{
\par \~
\par }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\ul\cf11 2. Adding extra items?}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 Yes its possible to do that as well.}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 If you're going to use the XML file for Product feeds, you'll simply need to add the extra fields in the XML}{
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 sheet, you can do that manually or by using an XML editor...}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 in }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\cf9 xml/products.xml}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 Product 1 for an example:}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 <CD>\line \~\~<PRODUCT>Product 1</PRODUCT>\line \~\~<DESCRIPTION>No description available yet</DESCRIPTION>\line \~\~<PRICE>120</PRICE>\line \~\~<PICTURE>geenprent.jpg</PICTURE>\line }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\cf6 \~ <COLOUR>#C0C0C0</COLOUR>}{

\par }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\cf6 \~\~<SIZE>10</SIZE>}{
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 \~</CD>}{
\par \~
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 AND, you will need to modify the }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\cf9 /js/products.js}{\f1\fs20\cf11  file as well, to populate the new fields in the arrays...}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 In the XML proccessing version of }{\cs15\b\f1\fs20\cf9 /js/products.js }{\f1\fs20\cf11 you'll find this code located somewhere at the bottom.}{
\par \~
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 It simply populates the Arrays, by reading the Childnodes out of the XML file, its quite straightforward
\par to add more fields to it.
\par }{\~}{\loch\af28\dbch\af28 
\par }{\f1\fs20\cf11 Product[i]=xmlObj.childNodes[i].childNodes(0).firstChild.text;\line Description[i]=xmlObj.childNodes[i].childNodes(1).firstChild.text;\line Price[i]=xmlObj.childNodes[i].childNodes(2).firstChild.text;\line 
Picture[i]=xmlObj.childNodes[i].childNodes(3).firstChild.text;}{
